I'm in a bit of a rut lately when it comes to moves and TV and need some suggestions. The more cerebral, imaginative, quirky, visual the better.Some examples of things I've really enjoyed in the past:- Senna- Le Mans- Paprika- Gattaca- Anything from Miyazaki, Kubrick- Little Miss Sunshine- Trinity and Beyond- The Fog of War- Cosmos- Connections- Amelie- Thank You for Smoking- Helvetica- Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex- Cowboy Bebop- The Girl Who Leapt Through Time- Babylon 5I've got the likes of Waltz with Bashir, Moon, and Pi in the queue, along with re-watching the likes of Big Fish, Syriana, The Sky Crawlers, et al. Otherwise I'm running out of ideas...
