I'd say watch as many Bud Spencer and Terrence Hill movies (they often star together).A lot of Bud Spencers movies pretend to be in the USA, but they're either in Spain if it's westerns, or in Panama if not (Banana Joe is in Colombia).Apart from the epic fight scenes, they're usually also have an underlying theme about fighting corruption, protecting the weak, the nature etc. The nature thing is especially prevaliant in the movies he wrote himself (the later ones).He's a very fascinating character, people probably didn't realise that he was the first Italian to swim the 100 meters under 1 minute, or were at the olympics on the Italian water polo team (or that he wrote the music, flew the planes and helicopters, directed some of the movies etc.).http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bud_SpencerTerence Hill is also a fascinating character, and I agree with him that My Name is Nobody is the best of his movies not together with Bud Spencer.http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terence_Hill---Here in Denmark you can pick the movies up on DVD for 2-4USD new, when you can find them. Or well, you know where they're available.I worked as a translator for quite some time, putting subtitles on English spoken movies. And once had to do a 10 pack of Bud Spencer movies. Worst job ever. All the actors speak Italian, and are dubbed to English, they were easy to subtitle. But Bud Spencer and Terrence Hill spoke English and where dubbed to Italian for that market, and unfortunatly Bud Spencer mumbles. Any ways, try picking one up, say, Banana Joe. Bud Spencer wrote the script for that one.
