WhiteKnight wrote:Zanshin wrote:A Scanner DarklyThis movie left me feeling schizophrenic. I dunno if that's a good thing or a bad thing. The weirdness of the movie makes more sense when you watch the extras. They tried to keep the movie close to the book, even bringing in members of Philip K Dick's estate to help them sort it all out. Apparently, Alyssa Milano's family and Philip's were relatively close (she lived on the same street as the Dick children when they were young, and they knew each other I think?), so that helped them all get together to make the movie. The book was his way to work through his own periods of heavy drug use, paranoia, and mental illness. So the story is actually Philip K Dick's commentary of how fucked up his own mind was.
