I'm not fond of Pi or Napoleon Dynamite, but I understand their appeal to people who are stupid and dumb and tasteless and broken inside. I would argue that Donnie Darko is objectively a bad and otherwise overhyped movie, but I doubt I'd get very far with that argument. The Cell is amongst the most visually stunning modern movies yet made (also see Tarsem's Immortals and The Fall, which I cited previously... and let's just forget about that J-Lo bit, m'kay?). Tarsem plots are weak, but that isn't the purpose of the movie. If you want to shit on the plot, so be it, but given the request made, The Cell fits perfectly on merit of the visuals/concept alone.Amelie and 5th Element, though? Each is universally recognized as being more or less the pinnacle of its genre. That is to say, you have no idea what the hell you're on about.
